# Python Rules (extends 00-core.mdc)

## Package Structure
- All importable code under `src/<project_name>/`. Use `src/` layout.
- `pyproject.toml` as single config file. `[build-system]` must always be present.
- `.venv` in project root for virtual environment.

## Separation of Concerns
- Core: pure domain logic — no I/O, no framework imports.
- Services: orchestrate core + adapters.
- Adapters: all I/O (filesystem, network, DB) — behind interfaces.

## Code Quality
- Explicit type hints on all public function signatures.
- Prefer small functions. No mutable module-level state.
- Use `dataclasses` or `TypedDict` for structured data — avoid raw dicts.

## Quality Gate
- Run `ruff check . && ruff format --check . && mypy src tests && pytest` after changes.
- Use code review checklist in `AGENTS.md` §7 before submitting.
